Quote:You guys realize we are talking about limited here right?Or at least we originally were till people just wanted to use this as a time to dump on how bad the current standard is.I think the current standard is actually really good. There are a lot of viable decks and things are changing at a fairly rapid pace. Mentor is decent in limited, not exactly a bomb but definitely a card to consider highly.EDITTo compare, think about it this way. He's a vanilla 2/2 for 2W and his ability requires another creature to trigger. Elvish Visionary was 1G for a vanilla 1/1 that immediately drew you a card. So even if your trigger creature is only a single mana it means that best case scenario Mentor is going to require 4W to cantrip. Obviously that gets better if you can trigger him more than once, but he is also very fragile.
Yam-Koo
Ars Tribunus Angusticlavius
Tribus: Portland, OR
Registered: Jul 18, 2000Posts: 6884
Posted: Tue Mar 06, 2012 11:08 pm
Being fragile (unless it's X/1 fragile) is pretty common in ISD, given the variety of removal in the format. His effect is huge and requires a kill/exile spell rather than just a tap/pacifism. The synergy with the large variety of white ETB creatures (doomed traveler, token makers, etc) means you almost certainly have a few sick synergies with him.On similar note, Loyal Cathar has been amazing for me. As long as I'm base white, he's great. Young Wolf has been similar. I like that they both enable demonmail hauberk, which I've been snapping up late and getting good value out of.i've also had some success with decks that are near-mono green. Green has been under picked in my experience, and I've been able to get pretty potent creatures decks going with some splash removal and prey upon keeping opponents under control.
Asmodan
Ars Tribunus Angusticlavius
Tribus: New Berlin, WI Gamertag: Asmodan
Registered: Jul 19, 2006Posts: 6191
Posted: Wed Mar 07, 2012 10:33 am
Quote:His effect is huge and requires a kill/exile spell rather than just a tap/pacifism. The synergy with the large variety of white ETB creatures (doomed traveler, token makers, etc) means you almost certainly have a few sick synergies with him.His effect isn't that huge unless you can trigger it multiple times. Yeah, it has some synergy with Doomed Traveler but if your big turn four play is making a spirit token and paying a mana so your three drop becomes a cantrip isn't what I'd define as huge. Again, most of the decks that want to run him don't want to make all their bears cost three instead of two. He's great if you have a reliable and repeatable way to trigger him (Stitcher's Apprentice for example) but otherwise you're running an aggro deck and kneecapping your curve to do it.EDIT:Again, don't think he's a bad card. But he's not a bomb and I wouldn't want to try to draft around him. He's a value card that you throw in to a W/X deck if you've got a reasonable amount of ways of triggering him. If you draw cards with him be happy, but he isn't a win condition.
