cobaltplasma wrote:In other news, speaking of Cube-talk, there's an MTGO one coming..sorta... kinda............. I'm a bit underwhelmed...http://www.wizards.com/Magic/Magazine/A ... arcana/927Initially playable only at PAX East for the weekend and then they're rerolling it out..somehow, sometime... /shrugs.I love the concept, but think it is collusully stupid to roll it out for such a short period of time. I'll never understand the MTGO ethos of "we'll put out a format, it will sell well, and we will then turn it off on an arbitrary date for no reason, because we hate people paying us $$ to play". Back when triple NPH draft was going on those things were firing left and right, I can't imagine how much $$ they were raking in, then one day, "Sorry, event is over, that thing you want to give us $$ to play, yeah, you go ahead and hold onto that cash, were good". Epically dumb. I took a look at the card list and it seems OK, there are some BROKEN cards that I pulled from my cube after a single session (Treachery). But 720 card is pretty big for a cube so your chances of seeing it go down. Quote:They won't say "we're printing foil power9!" but I think the suits will be giving the raised eyebrow stare more often.Not anytime soon, but I have zero doubt that day will come. The second profits start to slip, the "promise" of the reserve list will get tossed out the window and they'll start reprinting duals and the like to goose profits. Reprinting reserve list cards is a gold mine, and most shareholders don't like their companies to sit on gold mines too long.
