Asmodan wrote:Quote:Is this one of the 4-pack sealed, 30 card minimum decks?That would make a little more sense given he has exactly four flip cards. Though he's still short a rare unless I keep missing one.That said, as much as I dislike the combination I'd go WR. You are going to run something like 12 or 13 lands, so you need to come up with about 17 playables. I'd try something along the lines of:Thraben HereticSilverchase FoxUnruly MobLoyal CatharMidnight GuardChapel GeistThrabel PurebloodsKessig WolfPyreheart WolfRusset WolvesTormented PariahNearheath StalkerBurden of GuiltGeistflameRolling TemblorFaithless LootingRolling Temblor is super sketch since it basically kills all your dudes, but sometimes you just need a reset button. The other option would be Mask, but it's so slow that I don't know that it's going to help you. Otherwise you can maindeck Urgent Exorcism. There are enough spirits and enchantments that it's honestly not terrible in the main.Yeah, it was 4 pack sealed. The fourth rare was vault of the archangel, which I think was by far my strongest card. Unfortunately my white and black weren't really deep enough to build a deck without splashing blue for reap the seagraf (without color fixing.)I played a deck very similar to what Asmodan suggested, but without the faithless looting and rolling temblor, adding the rakish heir and crossway vampire. Round 1 I played a bad player playing green redwith big green dudes and removal (2xprey upon, harvest pyre, brimstone volley.) Game 1 I won a close one thanks to him making a couple of misplays. I didn't see how my aggro deck could get through fast enough before his creatures were all bigger than mine (2x villagers of estwald in particular) so I swapped decks into BWu hoping to get vault online. Game 2 I mulled a 6 land hand into a 1 land hand with a 2 drop and a bunch of three drops. I never drew a third land, and he finally killed me around turn 8 or so. Game 3 was close, with me stabilizing at 2 life and beating in for a while, but I drew 4 lands in a row and he drew a brimstone volley to finish it (with 11 cards left in our decks and me with all but 1 land in play.)Round 2 I played a deck with skirsdag high priest, midnight haunting, tragic slip, tribute to hunger, a couple doomed travelers, and some other stuff. Both games he had the priest out early. The first game, I thought I could double geistflame it since he only had 1 black up, but he used tragic slip on one of his spirits and made a 5/5 that I couldn't deal with. Game 2 I never drew anything to kill it and he killed me with multiple 5/5s.Round 3 I played a fast RB deck. Game 1 he opened with reckless waif into neonate into removal into removal, and I got steamrolled. Game 2 I swapped into BW and I curved perfectly into a turn 5 active vault of the archangel and destroyed him (despite turn 1 waif again). Game 3 he opened with turn 1 diregraf ghoul, turn 2 walking corpse. I traded every chance I could, and I ended up stabilizing with massive regenerating unruly mob and a handful of 2/2s. I had him one turn away from lethal, and he flipped traitorous blood to steal my untapped guy, hit me down to 1, and then cast fires of undeath.It was a massively frustrating experience all in all.
