Posted: Wed Mar 14, 2012 1:10 pm
Quote:I don't think the stacking damage thing was that big a deal. All it did was make sac effects stronger than they should have been.Fuck me running... we agree on something. Damage on the stack also led to a bunch of situations where it was not very intuitive (wait... he is about to hit me, but you sacrifice him... and he still hits me after he's dead?).I'm also not a fan of the titans. They are so overwhelmingly strong that it is extremely difficult to justify anything else in that slot. It even bleeds down to the five drop slot, because honestly they're generally so far and away better than any of those that it's hard not to just say 'I'll pay one more and just play a titan'. I'm also not fond of the fact that so many *other* potentially cool creatures at or around that cost get passed over because they just can't compete. Really a six mana creature in standard *should* do something big and impressive (and likely win you the game) but the titans are not big impressive dudes. They give so much value even if they are immediately removed it's difficult to claw back even if you deal with them. Primeval Titan is probably the worst offender, closely followed by Grave and Sun Titans. Sure, you kill their six drop Prime Time, but now they're sitting on a two or three turn clock with the Inkmoth Nexus and Kessig Wolf Run they dug up.
