Pysgard wrote:Yam-Koo wrote:Just crushed a draft with Endless Ranks of the Dead. Do I get an achievement for winning a game despite drawing 5 lands in a row, late game? Yeah, I've never had luck with zombies, even with the captain.I just 3-0'd another swiss, 3rd in a row. G/W humans was so ridiculously open. I had 3 gatstaf shephards, I was getting 8th pick priests and pilgrims of Avacyn, elder of laurels, deranged outcast, collar of avacyn, etc. Only lost 1 game to mana screw.On the other hand, went a pathetic 1-2 in a 4pk draft. The idea of those things is appealing, but yeah, I may have finally reached the point where I'd rather draft a good deck than try to open well.That sounds pretty sweet and congrats. However, you really need to move out of Swiss into 8-4. Same level of prize support (as compared to 4-3-2-2 which pays out one less pack for no good reason) as Swiss and the level of competition is much much higher.
